This paper deals with the connectivity and interference of sensors, which are typically studied in the field of networked sensing and communication (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of random variables and probability theory, which are common in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The concept of interference is also relevant to the field of signal processing and machine learning (cs.SI). Finally, the use of mathematical analysis and proofs suggests that this paper may also be relevant to the field of mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
